The paper discusses mathematical features of the loss landscape of overparameterized neural networks, which is a topic closely related to machine learning and optimization. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also mentions the use of neural networks in computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI), which further supports these sub-categories as likely choices. Additionally, the paper discusses the dimensionality of the locus of global minima, which is a topic related to numerical analysis and optimization (cs.NE) and topology (cs.SI).
